# **PowerShell Cmdlets Cheat Sheet** 🖥️⚡

## 🔹 Process & System Information
- **List top 10 CPU-consuming processes:**  
  `Get-Process | Sort-Object CPU -Descending | Select-Object -First 10`
- **Get detailed system information:**  
  `Get-ComputerInfo`
- **Format detailed system info as a list:**  
  `Get-ComputerInfo | Format-List *`
- **Retrieve OS details (Caption, Version, Architecture):**  
  `Get-CimInstance Win32_OperatingSystem | Select-Object Caption, Version, OSArchitecture`
- **List system accounts with full names:**  
  `Get-CimInstance Win32_UserAccount | Select-Object Name, FullName`

## 🔹 File Search & Management
- **Search for `the-lion-of-anacostia-bias-detection.md` system-wide:**  
  `Get-ChildItem -Path C:\ -Recurse -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue -Filter "the-lion-of-anacostia-bias-detection.md"`
- **Find all files with a `.md.md` typo in the filename:**  
  `Get-ChildItem -Path C:\ -Recurse -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue -Filter "*.md.md"`
- **Search for `the-lion-of-anacostia-bias-detection` (regardless of extension) system-wide:**  
  `Get-ChildItem -Path C:\ -Recurse -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue -Filter "the-lion-of-anacostia-bias-detection*"`
- **Search for all three conditions in one command:**  
  ```powershell
  Get-ChildItem -Path C:\ -Recurse -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object {
      $_.Name -eq "the-lion-of-anacostia-bias-detection.md" -or
      $_.Name -match "\.md\.md$" -or
      $_.BaseName -eq "the-lion-of-anacostia-bias-detection"
  }
  ```
- **Fix `.md.md` typos in filenames system-wide:**  
  ```powershell
  Get-ChildItem -Path C:\ -Recurse -Filter "*.md.md" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Rename-Item -NewName { $_.Name -replace "\.md\.md$", ".md" }
  ```
- **Create an empty file:**  
  `New-Item -Path "C:\path\to\file.txt" -ItemType File`
- **List the most recent 10 modified files on the system:**  
  ```powershell
  Get-ChildItem -Path "C:\" -Recurse -File | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 10
  ```

## 🔹 System & User Management
- **Check the current user and their SID:**  
  `whoami /user`
  Example Output:
  ```
  USER INFORMATION
  ----------------
  User Name           SID
  mrk73notebook\miker S-1-5-21-1211264659-1017429877-2648101728-1001
  ```

## 🔹 Software & PowerShell Management
- **Uninstall Dropbox via winget:**  
  `winget uninstall Dropbox`
- **Restart PowerShell with Admin privileges:**  
  `Start-Process pwsh -Verb RunAs; exit`

